timeline.bodyText:
codacy already recommended using StringBuilder here and I like that but I think is more maintainable doing something like :
mappingForField =  String.format("{\n"type":"%s"\n}",fieldType);
and pass fieldType. That way we can have that string format declared just once.
and the fieldType can be returned out of function so the function I imagine could use a static map and look like this:
ImmutableMap.of(
DataTypes.BOOL,DataTypes.BOOL.toString().toLowercase(),   //Could do something like this 
DataTypes.FLOAT, "float",   //or simply
DataTypes.INTEGER, "integer"
) ;

I've seen that Using maps like this to eliminate nested ifs. Is called the anti-if pattern.

